A compilation of British electronic music from 1992-1996.

‘Happy Land’ takes its title from the Ultramarine track with Robert Wyatt, included here, and also doubles as an ironic metaphor for the state of the UK in the early ‘90s, suffering socio-economic deprivation due to a Tory government who incidentally hated rave music.
